casebody.data:
Billy Jack PHILLIPS v. J. C. TAYLOR, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 7249. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Jan. 15, 1963. No appearance for appellant. Newell A. George, U. S. Atty., and Benjamin E. Franklin, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before MURRAH Chief Judge, and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed January 15, 1963, on ground appeal is now moot.
